{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder). A unit test of only one helper can miss wiring bugs where full-file content is accidentally passed through. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on model output quality.","test_description":"Wire real local modules that read a unified diff fixture and build the review payload; assert payload contains only changed hunks/line ranges and excludes untouched file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test needs cross-module wiring; pure unit is too low, higher levels are unnecessary.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and API behavior. In-process fakes can accept invalid positions that GitHub would reject or remap, hiding real failures.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions and verify each appears on the intended diff line in the PR UI/API.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Real HTTP/API behavior is the failure boundary, so System is required.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment (finding a true defect). Stubbed outputs would always pass and cannot validate defect-detection quality. Rejected higher level: behavior text asks for o